sequenceDiagram
    participant SP as Sidepanel
    participant SW as Service Worker
    participant CM as Cache Manager
    participant API as Gmail API
    participant Gmail as Gmail Tab

    Note over SP,Gmail: Panel Open / Reconnect
    SP->>SW: initWindow {windowId}
    SP->>SW: selectionChanged {labelId, scopeTimestamp}
    Note over SP: Settings loaded from chrome.storage.local (no port sync needed)
    SW->>SW: find active Gmail tab
    SW->>Gmail: tabs.update(url) — navigate to match filter
    SW->>CM: setFilterConfig(...)
    SW->>SP: resultsReady {accountPath}
    SW->>CM: start(accountPath)

    Note over SP,Gmail: Labels + Cache Build
    CM->>API: fetchLabels()
    API-->>CM: labels[]
    CM->>SW: progress callback (phase: labels)
    SW->>SP: labelsReady {labels}
    Note over SP: Store labels, skip render if label selected (wait for filterResults)
    loop For each label (parallel, up to concurrency)
        CM->>API: fetchLabelMessageIdsPage(labelId)
        API-->>CM: {ids, nextPageToken}
        CM->>CM: crossReferenceLabel — store labelIdx
    end
    CM->>SW: pushResults via callback
    SW->>SP: filterResults {counts, coLabelCounts, partial}
    Note over SP: Render filtered labels + counts

    Note over SP,Gmail: Warm Reconnect (orchestrator already running)
    SP->>SW: initWindow {windowId}
    SP->>SW: selectionChanged {labelId, scopeTimestamp}
    SW->>SP: resultsReady {accountPath}
    SW->>SP: labelsReady {labels} (from cache)
    SW->>SP: filterResults (immediate push from cached data)
